{
  "texts": [
    "NI, from a small pet up to humans, exhibits a vast range of cognitive characteristics.",
    "Humans and some animals present emotional intelligence, creativity, problem-solving, and decisionmaking under pressure, unknown surrounding factors, and conditions of uncertainty [49].",
    "These capabilities seem to be inherently natural and cannot be replicated by current AI systems.",
    "On the other hand, NI is constrained by biological limitations such as short memory size, decision and calculation processing speed, and susceptibility to cognitive biases.",
    "We also showed that under the current methods and practices of AI, the current implementations cannot raise the amount of Shannon Entropy of their dataset, without the presence and contribution of humans."
  ]
}